<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>The Quest for Exotic Ingredients (help needed)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Korbac">Korbac</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:04 p.m. 14/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> The Quest for Exotic Ingredients (help needed)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>So one day I was visiting my favorite shady tavern in Freeport, when the bartender there told me of a beverage he wished to make if I could bring him the following four ingredients:

<P>Kiola Nut, which is found on the various ocean islands.
<P>Honey Jum, made by a shopkeeper in Rivervale.
<P>Koalindl Fish, found only in the pool of the Temple of Life in Qeynos.
<P>Erud's Tonic, made in Erudin, but illegal to smuggle from the city.
<P>So far I have managed to procure the Kiola Nut and the Honey Jum, but I'll be damned if I can figure out how to get a Koalindl Fish (I have not attempted to get the Erud's Tonic yet). Does ANYONE have any idea how I'm supposed to get a Koalindl? There seems to be a side quest - a dog named Frostbite occasionally steals one of the fish from the pool, and the Guard there asks you to recover it for him. I've tried killing the dog (which seriously ticked off the owners), and I've tried talking to the owners, but still can't figure it out.
<P>Anybody have an idea? Oh, and fishing in the pool only gets you normal fish.
<P>Thanks in advance for any help, and if you happen to be on Bristlebane, I'll pay you 2 platinum if you either bring me the fish or help me to get it.
<P>Korbac
<BR>Half Elf Scout of Tunare
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
